Why bother to move our criteria logic into a class implementing [`Predicate`][14]? If you ever need that logic in more than one place, you now have a simple way to re-use that logic. Also, that interface happens to be a [functional interface][15] (an interface requiring only a single method) which can then be used with Java Streams (see [this](http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/collections/streams/index.html) and [this](http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/articles/java/ma14-java-se-8-streams-2177646.html)) and [Lambda expressions][16] for some very powerful code with very short (simple?) syntax.


