`data` is not a list (or array) of arrays. It is an implementation of the interface [`oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleResultSet`][1]. So you cannot iterate over it using a for-each loop.

It also implements [`ResultSet`][2], which defines the method `next()`.
Therefore you can iterate over `data` using a `while-loop`:

&lt;!-- Language: lang-java --&gt;

    while (data.next()){
        Object obj = data.getObject(col);
        // do somthing with obj
    }

The method `next()` moves the cursor to the next row.
`col` can either be the column index or label.

[Here][3] you can find an example on using `ResultSet`.


  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E11882_01/appdev.112/e13995/oracle/jdbc/OracleResultSet.html
  [2]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/sql/ResultSet.html
  [3]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/jdbc/basics/retrieving.html

