Your configuration and properties are correct. The circuit breaker will open only after the `minimumNumberOfCalls` are recorded.

The reason for the above ProductResponse is due to the [fallback mechanism of Resilience4J][1].

&gt; If a fallback method is configured, every exception is forwarded to a fallback method executor. The fallback method executor is searching for the best matching fallback method which can handle the exception

Henceforth, narrow down the scope of argument of fallback method from `Exception` to `CallNotPermittedException`

```
public ProductResponse demoServiceFallbackMethod(Integer id, CallNotPermittedException exc) {
            logger.error(&quot;Got an error, executing fallbackmethod and returning default from application&quot;);
            return defaultProduct();
     }
```



  [1]: https://resilience4j.readme.io/docs/getting-started-3#fallback-methods

